    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "### Problem\n\nWhen saving multiple files with `:wa`, only one file is shown in UI2 \"msg\" area.\nProbably because \"bufwrite\" messages for every file share ID and since \"bufwrite\" is of kind \"progress\" - message gets updated. And since it's done quickly, visually it looks like a single file written.\n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\nnvim --clean\n:lua require(\"vim._core.ui2\").enable({ enable = true, msg = { target = \"cmd\", targets = { progress = \"msg\" } } })\n:e a.txt\n<make any change, don't save>\n:e b.txt\n<make any change, don't save>\n:wa\n\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nEvery affected file is mentioned separately.\n\n### Nvim version (nvim -v)\n\nv0.13.0-dev commit 9734f33bc7\n\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\n\nn/a\n\n### Operating system/version\n\nmacOS Tahoe 26.4.1 (25E253) arm64\n\n### Terminal name/version\n\nGhostty 1.3.2-main-+c74f6d56d\n\n### $TERM environment variable\n\nxterm-ghostty\n\n### Installation\n\nbuild from source",
